-- Telekom Slovenije First-Half Net Rises 5% to 26.5 Million Euros
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-08-30T07:47:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-30/telekom-slovenije-first-half-net-rises-5-to-26-5-million-euros.html
Telekom Slovenije Group d.d.  said
net income in the first six months gained 5 percent from a year
earlier to 26.5 million euros ($33 million) as the Slovenian
state-owned company cuts costs.  Revenue dropped 3 percent to 391 million euros, the
Ljubljana-based company said in a  regulatory filing  today.
Telekom Slovenije lowered its net debt by 27 percent to 325.8
million euros, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
